Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.18,0:00:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.77,0:00:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.96,0:00:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.83,0:00:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.25,0:00:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Kasia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.29,0:00:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here with my colleagues,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.37,0:00:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuchen and James.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.56,0:00:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are here to hand you the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.56,0:00:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,keys to a better text input
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.99,0:00:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,experience in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.25,0:00:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see what we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.52,0:00:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to start with
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.44,0:00:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,integrating the keyboard into
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.69,0:00:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're also going to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.79,0:00:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about creating dynamic and more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.27,0:00:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting input accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.56,0:00:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,views.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.45,0:00:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll talk about making your app
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.32,0:00:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,reach multilingual audiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.59,0:00:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,using traits to make predictive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.06,0:00:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,quick type smarter in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.80,0:00:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Supporting hardware keyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.67,0:00:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Creating custom input views.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.69,0:01:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, tips and best
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,practices for keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.15,0:01:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,extensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.35,0:01:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.53,0:01:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,integrating the keyboard into
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.67,0:01:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, I'm going to show
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.82,0:01:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you a screenshot of the app
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.29,0:01:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we've created for this talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.30,0:01:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called CatChat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.50,0:01:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for talking with your pets.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.42,0:01:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just cats, but in my case,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,just cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.45,0:01:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do have this available as
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.44,0:01:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,sample code so you can grab it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.62,0:01:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from the site.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.48,0:01:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Cat pictures not included.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.70,0:01:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's get started with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.03,0:01:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to see a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.64,0:01:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this in the talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.25,0:01:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to start with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.79,0:01:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,accounting for changing keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.35,0:01:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.98,0:01:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, keyboards come in different
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.71,0:01:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.22,0:01:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on the language that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.98,0:01:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the user is using and the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.33,0:01:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,settings that they've enabled,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.03,0:01:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you might see different heights
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.61,0:01:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the keyboards that are used
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.92,0:01:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.82,0:01:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The English keyboard, with the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,predictive bar, is one height,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.27,0:01:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas the Polish keyboard is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.88,0:01:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,shorter, and the Chinese 10-key
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.25,0:01:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,pinyin keyboard, is taller than
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,both of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.72,0:01:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are third party
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.07,0:01:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboards, which some of you may
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.36,0:01:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have even written, and those do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.95,0:02:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,not have a specific height
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.25,0:02:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,requirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.50,0:02:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're not ever guaranteed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.07,0:02:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a specific height for a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.53,0:02:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard that a user is using in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.88,0:02:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how do you account for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.26,0:02:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have a set of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We tell you when the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.44,0:02:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,shows, when it hides, and when
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.78,0:02:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the frame changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.14,0:02:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And for each of these
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications, we'll give you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.90,0:02:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning and ending frame
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.66,0:02:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you get from the keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.88,0:02:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now before we go into how to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.76,0:02:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,work with that frame we're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.55,0:02:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,giving you, let's talk about a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.85,0:02:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,bit of a special case, and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.39,0:02:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the undocked keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In iPads, the user can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.59,0:02:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,lift the keyboard off the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.79,0:02:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the screen, and move it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,around, as well as split it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.00,0:02:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instance, you generally
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.13,0:02:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want your app to be trying
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.74,0:02:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay on top of the keyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.99,0:02:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because they might move it all
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.74,0:02:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to the top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.53,0:02:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, and then all your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,content is gone and that's no
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.85,0:02:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.71,0:02:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when the keyboard gets
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.27,0:02:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,undocked, we will send you a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.60,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hide" notification, just like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.32,0:02:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we would if the keyboard was
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.24,0:02:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In most cases, that's how you're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:02:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,going to handle it, as though
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the keyboard was dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.91,0:03:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do want to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,clever, we will continue sending
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you frame change notifications,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but for most people, what you're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,going to want to do is track the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.29,0:03:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,most recent hide or show event,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.58,0:03:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and then deal with the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,accordingly before you deal with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.90,0:03:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,any frame changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the undocked keyboard is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.07,0:03:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have this nice scroll view.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.89,0:03:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the keyboard comes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the scroll view compensates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's undocked, it takes up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the full screen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.81,0:03:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the user docks it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,again, it comes back up so that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.63,0:03:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,transcript of your delightful
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.38,0:03:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,chat with your cat, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.86,0:03:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the kind of special
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.59,0:03:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's move on to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,working with that frame
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.26,0:03:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,notification that we give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.67,0:03:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First things first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.31,0:03:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The keyboard is always full
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.23,0:03:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always in the full screen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.63,0:03:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.19,0:03:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the first thing you do when
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.15,0:03:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a keyboard frame from
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.31,0:03:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,one of our notifications, is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.86,0:03:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,convert it from the frame -- the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.10,0:03:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,screen coordinates, to your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.20,0:03:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,local coordinates before you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.66,0:03:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,start working with anything
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.54,0:03:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.76,0:04:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the keyboard can be full
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,screen when you are not, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.48,0:04:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can you know --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.69,0:04:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there are all sorts of fun
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.52,0:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,situations where keyboards come
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,up and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You always want to make sure to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,do this first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.24,0:04:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't count on the frame
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.13,0:04:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that you get being local to the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.84,0:04:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,frame of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about multitasking, for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.08,0:04:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.74,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if you do use the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,intersection of the frame that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.09,0:04:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we give you once you've
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.84,0:04:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,converted it, and the view you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.41,0:04:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,want to use, you can then get
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.06,0:04:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference in height between
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the two of those -- or the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.39,0:04:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,height of the keyboard as it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.81,0:04:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will overlap your view, and use
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that to adjust for the keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's talk about a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.45,0:04:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,different kinds of layouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with layouts that do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.58,0:04:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,not scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, static layouts are generally
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of text views, maybe a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,button, where the user doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.54,0:04:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,have to move around a lot in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.21,0:04:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,order to see everything in your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.87,0:04:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But you still want it to look
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,nice with all keyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.84,0:04:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In this instance, as an example,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.45,0:04:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we have five text fields and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.72,0:04:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they are tied together with UI
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout Guides acting as spacers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:04:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,AT the top of the view, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.25,0:05:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,using The Safe Area Edge Insets,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.60,0:05:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the bottom -- well, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.21,0:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about that in a second, but
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.06,0:05:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the spacers change size
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on what keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.16,0:05:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,appears, so that it always shows
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,all five of the text views to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.88,0:05:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how did we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.68,0:05:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we created a custom UI
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.05,0:05:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout Guide with a height
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.68,0:05:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint that we hold onto so
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.45,0:05:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can adjust it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.04,0:05:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Layout Guide gets tied to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.68,0:05:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom Safe Area Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Guide of your view.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.17,0:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the top of the Layout Guide
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.18,0:05:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,should be tied to the bottom of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the view or spacer that you want
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to appear directly on top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.64,0:05:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard, when the keyboard has
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.93,0:05:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you do that, you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.18,0:05:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your height conversion after
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.75,0:05:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,checking that the keyboard is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.66,0:05:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,visible, and simply set that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,height constraint you held onto,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.37,0:05:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to the height of the keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.27,0:05:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you pop that into a view
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.43,0:05:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,animation block with N call
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.26,0:05:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,layout if needed, you'll get the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,cool little animation between
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.63,0:05:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the keyboards that you saw, just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.23,0:05:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.71,0:05:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The more common case however,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.61,0:05:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are scrolling layouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.36,0:06:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Layouts embedded in the scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,view so that the user can move
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.96,0:06:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,between your views, and see
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.56,0:06:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that they need to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.54,0:06:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In our case, we had this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.53,0:06:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation View Controller in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,our Cat Chat app.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.21,0:06:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.08,0:06:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you can scroll through the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.94,0:06:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,entire conversation at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.54,0:06:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we need to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom of the table view is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.09,0:06:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusted to how the entirety of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your chat transcript.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.25,0:06:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how do you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.91,0:06:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Very similar to before but a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.28,0:06:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,little less complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.62,0:06:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You simply make sure the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard's visible gain, do your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,frame conversion, get your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.67,0:06:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,height, and set the content
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.65,0:06:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,inset of the scroll view.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where that intersection
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.67,0:06:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,bit is helpful because if you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.10,0:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,have a scroll view that does not
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,take up the full screen, you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.98,0:06:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,only want to offset it by the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,bit that's covered by the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.27,0:06:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, you do need to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.54,0:06:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolling the content, once
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.25,0:06:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you've adjusted your scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.30,0:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.77,0:06:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In the previous example, we were
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.08,0:06:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,actually using a UI Table View
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.65,0:06:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller, which is even easier
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.44,0:06:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because it sets the insets for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.03,0:06:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you, and all you have to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.89,0:07:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll the content, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.43,0:07:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we have a table
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.08,0:07:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,view and we want the most recent
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,item to show right above the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.35,0:07:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we scroll the bottom cell,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.80,0:07:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the bottom of our inset table
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.43,0:07:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that is adjusting for the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.40,0:07:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard in your layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about extending
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the keyboard with an input
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory view.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.02,0:07:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The input accessory view, is a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.22,0:07:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,view right above the keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.45,0:07:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, it's a text view, and a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.09,0:07:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.13,0:07:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,IT can also be a tool bar with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,some navigation buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.49,0:07:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be a row of buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.12,0:07:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If can a couple of cool little,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.29,0:07:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, photos or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.35,0:07:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you want to put on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.53,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there, you can because it's just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you add this to the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.58,0:07:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.28,0:07:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here we have the -- an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.51,0:07:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,input accessory view in our chat
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.35,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, it's the host view
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,controller that wants to display
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.73,0:07:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the keyboard with the input
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.58,0:07:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory view.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we make it part of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.15,0:07:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,responder chain by returning
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.84,0:07:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,True for, "Can become first
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.12,0:07:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,responder," on our conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.45,0:07:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, using either a custom view
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.57,0:08:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or a custom view controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.12,0:08:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on what exactly you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.38,0:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,want to do with that view, you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.28,0:08:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,override the applicable method.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.51,0:08:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Input accessory view, if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.01,0:08:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,using a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Input accessory view controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.69,0:08:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're using a view
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.23,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.35,0:08:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the input accessory view
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.93,0:08:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that you add, is accounted for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in frame change notifications,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and if the height of that input
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory view changes, it will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.85,0:08:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,send a frame change
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.09,0:08:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can take care of that in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.72,0:08:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the app that the keyboard is in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about making a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.03,0:08:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic height changing input
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.59,0:08:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory view, because this is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.72,0:08:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,something that a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.57,0:08:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be able to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're doing this, this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,acts a lot like a self-sizing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,table view in that you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.55,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,take whatever view is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,be changing size, and use it to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.46,0:08:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,define the height of the view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do this with more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.53,0:08:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,than one, but in this example,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.71,0:08:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll use a UI text view to show
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,how this might be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.65,0:08:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you pin -- you can pin it to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.23,0:08:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the top and bottom of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.32,0:08:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,content view with spacing if
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.30,0:08:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there are views in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,between it, that's fine as long
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as the height is fully defined.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, it's very similar to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.62,0:09:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,self-sizing table view cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.67,0:09:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, you need to use
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.72,0:09:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or define the intrinsic content
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.22,0:09:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,size of your growing view, so
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.92,0:09:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that the input accessory view
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.30,0:09:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,knows how talk it needs to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,With a text view specifically,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.88,0:09:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in order for it to have its own
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.02,0:09:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic content size so that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.47,0:09:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to define it, you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,need to tell its text container
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.70,0:09:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to have its height track the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.98,0:09:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,text view.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.32,0:09:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And you also need to disable
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.98,0:09:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.15,0:09:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, the text view
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.65,0:09:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,defines its internal --
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.52,0:09:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic content size, based on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.97,0:09:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the amount of text in the view.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.49,0:09:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can get something like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.56,0:09:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.80,0:09:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is one of the few cases
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.55,0:09:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,where you may need to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,override intrinsic content size
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.40,0:09:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the input accessory view.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.41,0:09:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, you don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.83,0:09:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to spend, you know -- don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.06,0:09:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it too complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.03,0:09:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually not too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab the bounds as they come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.64,0:09:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to be your original
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.56,0:09:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,bounds, and we'll make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the correct width,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.16,0:09:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which is already given to you by
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.09,0:09:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.47,0:09:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In my case, I always like to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.89,0:10:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that the view has a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.09,0:10:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,minimum height, so I set it to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,minimum height first, just in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.38,0:10:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,case everything else -- all my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.13,0:10:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,other ifs are elses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.24,0:10:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, if my expanding view
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.68,0:10:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is the correct height, I use
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.10,0:10:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that plus some vertical padding
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've previously defined to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,define the new height of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I also have a maximum height
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.50,0:10:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's only so much I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,actually should type to my cats
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have great attention
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,spans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.21,0:10:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at a point, it stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.13,0:10:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, you simply return
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.87,0:10:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your new intrinsic content size,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.58,0:10:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and your input accessory view
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.14,0:10:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,will grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.09,0:10:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we have now talked
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.65,0:10:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,about integrating the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.79,0:10:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,into your layout, and adding a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.33,0:10:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic input accessory view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.58,0:10:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have an app where I can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.98,0:10:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to my cats, and I can say
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,more than a couple of words at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.23,0:10:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,once, which is nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.87,0:10:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't need very many words.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He's very specific in what he
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.22,0:10:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,needs from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's more cool things
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.76,0:10:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can do with this app to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.55,0:10:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,make it a lot more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.74,0:10:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to hand this over
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.70,0:10:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to Shuchen, and she's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:10:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you all about how to make
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.85,0:11:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your app feel more magical.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.52,0:11:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.18,0:11:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.28,0:11:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS, we provide a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.76,0:11:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sweet features so that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.15,0:11:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,improve our user text input
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.78,0:11:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.93,0:11:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Shuchen Li.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.54,0:11:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk a few of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.73,0:11:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I hope after my talk you can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,utilize these tricks and make
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.53,0:11:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your app feel magical.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.23,0:11:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first of all, let me ask a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.11,0:11:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.64,0:11:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are multilingual people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.57,0:11:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see quite a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, am I. Do you face the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.67,0:11:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,situation that you have to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.82,0:11:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,switch keyboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see one there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.28,0:11:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see a few of you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. I suffer that problem too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.70,0:11:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have to talk to my boss
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.57,0:11:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with one keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.67,0:11:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I talk to my mom with another
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.85,0:11:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.34,0:12:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to keep switch between
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.64,0:12:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What if your app just know what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.23,0:12:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.71,0:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What if when keyboard brings up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.36,0:12:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just the right keyboard for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you may know this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.98,0:12:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In our Message app, it does that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.63,0:12:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I talk to John with English
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.20,0:12:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I talk to my [inaudible] with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.35,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.07,0:12:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And Magic knows what keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm using.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.62,0:12:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.03,0:12:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS, we can associate a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,unique identifier called Text
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.63,0:12:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Input Context Identifier, with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,your text view.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.41,0:12:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, we can associate that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with all your UI Responder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, you can also do that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with your view controllers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when we see you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.58,0:12:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,unique identifier set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.15,0:12:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're a responder, we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.82,0:12:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will associate that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.12,0:12:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically with the user
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.08,0:13:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,selected keyboard, and then save
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.41,0:13:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that into user default.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.47,0:13:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, when you are a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,responder, becomes a first
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.61,0:13:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,responder, the keyboard will be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,retrieved automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.37,0:13:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you need to worry
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.34,0:13:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about is to find a good unique
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.05,0:13:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What are good unique
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.20,0:13:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.12,0:13:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, your user ID, your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.08,0:13:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation ID, the group IDs,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.72,0:13:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all good examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you may ask, "Where should I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,put this unique identifier?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.92,0:13:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You mentioned, yes, I can define
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.48,0:13:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it in all the UI responder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.61,0:13:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I define it everywhere?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.93,0:13:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.43,0:13:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see how we put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.41,0:13:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's recall our CatChat app.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.20,0:13:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When we bring out the keyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the text view becomes the first
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,responder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.18,0:13:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what's next, in the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,responder chain, is our
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.58,0:13:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.73,0:13:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, it's navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.09,0:13:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.04,0:14:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in iOS, when we look
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.81,0:14:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for the unique identifier for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your responder, we will search
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and look up the responder chain
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.96,0:14:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to look for the first one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.95,0:14:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in our app, we handle all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.47,0:14:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our conversation in our
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.55,0:14:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.19,0:14:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we put it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.82,0:14:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In such way, you don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.15,0:14:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,find a way you pass down your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.21,0:14:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,unique identifier to your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.65,0:14:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] or other places that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.96,0:14:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it want to pass in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.14,0:14:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you just put in where you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.30,0:14:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,handle all your conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how we transfer all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these into code.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In our conversation view
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.92,0:14:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, we override the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.86,0:14:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] for Text Input
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.45,0:14:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Context Identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.97,0:14:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.92,0:14:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just return a unique
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.12,0:14:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In our case, we return our
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.08,0:14:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,recipient's ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.02,0:14:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Kasia is going to show you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.72,0:14:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a demo to see how we give our
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.89,0:14:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,app a memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:14:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Kasia?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:15:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.81,0:15:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You may not remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.70,0:15:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,seen you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.73,0:15:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But Kasia's still on keyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so first -- here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.90,0:15:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,our CatChat app that we've been
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got a couple of pets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.01,0:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that speak different languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.42,0:15:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my Misiu here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.24,0:15:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He speaks Polish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually, I learned as a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,child that all cats speak
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.34,0:15:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Polish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.80,0:15:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's important to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.88,0:15:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Polish to all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.56,0:15:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But, my default keyboard as an
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.26,0:15:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,English speaker is English.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.20,0:15:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I go ahead and change it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.12,0:15:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to Polish, and say "Hello,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.19,0:15:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.54,0:15:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And see, you know, how he's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,doing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.11,0:15:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is me saying, "Hey, how are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you doing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.57,0:15:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wants food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.48,0:15:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's check in on
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.49,0:15:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuchen's dog, Jiwang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jiwang would like to go out
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.17,0:15:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for a walk, but I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.50,0:15:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,currently have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.82,0:16:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he speaks Chinese, so
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to switch keyboards
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.97,0:16:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,again to the Chinese pinyin
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.21,0:16:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard, and say, "I don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.43,0:16:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,time right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.68,0:16:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be patient."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.33,0:16:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And dogs are a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,friendlier sometimes with their
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,responses than cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.24,0:16:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now, this is the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.92,0:16:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've used this to talk to both
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.09,0:16:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I go back into Misiu's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.11,0:16:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation, the Polish
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.97,0:16:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I go back here, I still
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have the Chinese keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.33,0:16:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't have to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.14,0:16:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,switching keyboards, depending
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.73,0:16:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on the conversation I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And all that needed to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.52,0:16:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for that to happen, was to set
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that text input context
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.53,0:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier, as Shuchen showed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.32,0:16:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you, with the unique ID of each
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.34,0:16:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,individual chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.52,0:16:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If I change languages now, my
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,app doesn't need to know what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.42,0:16:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,language I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It just needs to know that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.43,0:16:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in a specific conversation and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.17,0:16:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we will take care of setting the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.15,0:16:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,proper keyboard for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.59,0:16:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.02,0:16:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.43,0:17:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, back to Shuchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.78,0:17:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Kasia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A quite neat feature, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.38,0:17:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll save quite a bit of wear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and tear on your [inaudible] I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.21,0:17:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this whole process, you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.05,0:17:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,may notice, you don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.14,0:17:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,need to care what keyboard the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.74,0:17:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,user selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.12,0:17:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you need to worry
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about is the unique identifier
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that was set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.62,0:17:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you may ask, what if you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.52,0:17:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,want to know what's the language
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.39,0:17:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the user used?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you want to develop a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.84,0:17:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,specific feature for a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,language?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you may want to look up UI
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,text input mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.14,0:17:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In UI text input mode, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.90,0:17:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,easily access the primary
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.73,0:17:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,language for the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In such way, you can for
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.16,0:17:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,example, develop your own spell
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.52,0:17:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,checker for your own language or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can develop other specific
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.14,0:17:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,feature for the specific
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.24,0:17:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,language that you want that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.85,0:17:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,probably [inaudible] support
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:17:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,where -- we will support maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.71,0:18:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.15,0:18:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, next, we've been working
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.94,0:18:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,really hard on how to accurately
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.38,0:18:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and quickly input text.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.65,0:18:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We made it further through a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.29,0:18:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,context scroll predictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.52,0:18:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we take user personalized
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.67,0:18:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,information into account.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.02,0:18:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in iOS 4, we introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.05,0:18:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard types.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.57,0:18:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's different keyboard types
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.63,0:18:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,like email keyboards, URL
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.22,0:18:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're typing an email
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.65,0:18:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,address, the @ and the .com keys
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.12,0:18:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are there for easy typing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, we introduced UI text
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,content type.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.42,0:18:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,UI text content type, it's a tag
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.34,0:18:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can set to your text
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.71,0:18:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It will provide all the context
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,predictions through the tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.17,0:19:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now, John wants to add his
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,cat, Penny, into our CatChat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.61,0:19:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is John Appleseed's cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From the video, you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.06,0:19:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,actually John didn't even type
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.74,0:19:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on any of the letter keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.46,0:19:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He was just typing on the Quick
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.43,0:19:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Type bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.62,0:19:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All the informations are input.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.32,0:19:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, John wants to type the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.93,0:19:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,address for the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.03,0:19:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's John Appleseed's cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.81,0:19:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it lives in -- must be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.42,0:19:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,living in an Apple store.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.49,0:19:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.78,0:19:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The one is Los Gatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For someone if we don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.93,0:19:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Los Gatos means "cat" in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.26,0:19:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.44,0:19:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we can see, John went to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.14,0:19:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,map and browsed the Apple store
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what's the address.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.06,0:19:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then come back to our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,CatChat app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.18,0:19:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you will see, ta-da,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the address are there,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.21,0:20:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,magically.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.79,0:20:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And by typing on the Quick Type
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.84,0:20:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,bar, you can -- thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.80,0:20:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If I type on the Quick Type bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.23,0:20:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you can directly input the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.34,0:20:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,address.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.63,0:20:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look closely, you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,its source.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.28,0:20:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from Map, in our case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.28,0:20:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS, we've been pulling
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,all user information and user
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.23,0:20:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,activities as a whole, to come
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.80,0:20:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with the data source, to improve
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.04,0:20:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,user's experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, our keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,personalization also can extract
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.97,0:20:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,names to form keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.11,0:20:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,personalization lexicon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.96,0:20:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, one more thing I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.97,0:20:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,mention.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.00,0:20:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In this whole process, your app
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.05,0:20:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is not only a passive receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.99,0:20:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Your app can be a contributor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.33,0:20:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Your app can contribute your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.83,0:21:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,app's activity through NS User
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.43,0:21:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Activity APIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.18,0:21:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, if your browse
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.40,0:21:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,your favorite restaurant in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.41,0:21:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yelp, the address can be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.15,0:21:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed on the Quick Type bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.91,0:21:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if you set the tag properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, sounds interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.37,0:21:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to learn more, don't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.61,0:21:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,forget to look at the session
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,from last year called "Increase
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.07,0:21:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Usage of Your App Through
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.80,0:21:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Proactive Suggestion."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this year, we made it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,further.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.17,0:21:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We add some new tags for user
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.73,0:21:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,name and password.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.37,0:21:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When you label your log-in field
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.73,0:21:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,properly, we will automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.70,0:21:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,suggest user name and password
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.58,0:21:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.96,0:21:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, fill that for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.54,0:21:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you need to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.40,0:21:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if you set your tags properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.79,0:22:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a one line API super
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.37,0:22:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,simple, and it will guarantee
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.55,0:22:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that some of the Quick Type
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.38,0:22:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,suggestion will display.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.62,0:22:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this is not the full
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.19,0:22:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,story.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.97,0:22:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to make sure all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.78,0:22:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,your credentials displayed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.03,0:22:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,properly with your app, because
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have a website to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.92,0:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,associate with your app, you'd
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,want to check out "Introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.62,0:22:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Password Auto Fill for App"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.13,0:22:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.92,0:22:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, next up, we talk about some
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.45,0:22:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,new smartness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.26,0:22:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we introduced some
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.86,0:22:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,smartness into our text view.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.24,0:22:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First one is Smart Quote.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.18,0:22:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are typewriter quotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.52,0:22:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They are straight and some
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.41,0:22:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,people don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.44,0:22:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,These are typographic quotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.67,0:22:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.21,0:22:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They are curly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.33,0:22:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're more legible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.87,0:23:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually, they're more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.10,0:23:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,grammatically correct in the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.75,0:23:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,language perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.08,0:23:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And this year, iOS will
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.39,0:23:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically convert your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.39,0:23:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,typewriter quote into
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.77,0:23:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,typographic quote.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.52,0:23:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.49,0:23:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.40,0:23:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When you type on the middle bar
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.94,0:23:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,line, sometimes you just think
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.96,0:23:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,about, "Okay, a hyphen, an end
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.88,0:23:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,dash, and add dash," how to do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.29,0:23:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.27,0:23:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,From this year, we can input a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.34,0:23:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,hyphen with one dash.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We will automatically convert
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.48,0:23:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,two dashes into an end dash.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.57,0:23:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, add dash with three
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.34,0:23:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,dashes of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.52,0:23:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.11,0:23:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we introduce Smart
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.92,0:23:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Insertion and Smart Deletion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.58,0:23:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you work with tags before,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.83,0:23:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to insert and delete a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.04,0:23:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,paragraph or a phrase, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.21,0:23:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.37,0:24:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And not even mention the trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.85,0:24:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,caused by punctuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.21,0:24:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, in our example,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.54,0:24:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Vivian wants to bring Jiwang
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.14,0:24:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,also to the party, but then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.07,0:24:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jiwang was sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.54,0:24:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have to remove him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.32,0:24:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this whole process, you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.05,0:24:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have to deal with a space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.86,0:24:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.35,0:24:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.60,0:24:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from today, we will take
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.45,0:24:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,care of all of that for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.17,0:24:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,With Smart Insertion and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.25,0:24:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Deletion, we'll take care of all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.87,0:24:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the leading and trailing spaces
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.83,0:24:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.52,0:24:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.71,0:24:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I want to mention, all the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.89,0:24:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,smartness that we introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.98,0:24:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have talked about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.33,0:24:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they are all by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.50,0:24:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want you note, for these
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.79,0:24:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,smart text input traits, they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.22,0:24:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,have three values.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.74,0:24:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They have yes, no, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.32,0:24:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,default value.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.87,0:24:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We set the default value for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.25,0:24:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,default for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.24,0:25:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We will automatically do the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.94,0:25:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,right thing for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.16,0:25:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if you have a text
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.34,0:25:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,field, you set the Secured Text
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.09,0:25:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Entry to Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.74,0:25:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably it's the password
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.08,0:25:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,field.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.63,0:25:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, if you set your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.96,0:25:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,smart traits to default, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.76,0:25:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically disable the smart
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.33,0:25:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,quote conversion for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.46,0:25:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because we think probably that's
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.88,0:25:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the user password.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.05,0:25:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to switch user
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.10,0:25:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,typing for a password field.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.05,0:25:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you recall, actually we can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.80,0:25:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,config auto correction types.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.82,0:25:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can config auto
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.78,0:25:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,capitalization types.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.29,0:25:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of sweet traits
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.01,0:25:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have in Text Input
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.11,0:25:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,traits.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.44,0:25:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them have this default
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.28,0:25:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,value.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.53,0:25:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What I want to emphasize here
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.08,0:25:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is, before you play with any of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.62,0:25:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,these traits, always understand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.72,0:25:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what your tags is going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.14,0:25:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Always understand what the tags
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.56,0:25:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you're expecting the user to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.79,0:25:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,type.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.81,0:26:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me ask another question.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.88,0:26:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Who flew to San Jose for WWDC?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.10,0:26:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.46,0:26:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, am I. Kidding this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.38,0:26:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a text entry, only
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.99,0:26:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,take flight code as an input, in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.37,0:26:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,such case, probably you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.95,0:26:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,disable auto correction type and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.92,0:26:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,auto capitalization type setting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.71,0:26:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.57,0:26:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? Because that makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.16,0:26:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you always want to fully
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.81,0:26:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,understand your text before set
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.40,0:26:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all these traits.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.13,0:26:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just, okay, type on the tab
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.80,0:26:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and just say, "Okay, yes," or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.09,0:26:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"No," just by thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Always fully understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.56,0:26:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.06,0:26:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, while work with text, you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.34,0:26:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,can now ignore marked texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.01,0:26:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Two big names, Chinese and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.70,0:26:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.14,0:26:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They all use marked texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.32,0:26:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, marked text language call
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.68,0:27:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,word, the marked text into final
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.53,0:27:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,text by select candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.55,0:27:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS, actually you can easily
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.80,0:27:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,access marked text from UI Text
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.83,0:27:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Input.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.91,0:27:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can directly use the marked
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.68,0:27:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,text.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.54,0:27:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an example in our system
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.90,0:27:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.81,0:27:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In Spotlight, when user type in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.08,0:27:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese for example, before
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.51,0:27:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,users select the candidate,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.41,0:27:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Spotlight engine already start
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.10,0:27:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to show you all the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.22,0:27:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also do that in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.16,0:27:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,through the marked text by
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.30,0:27:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,retrieving it from UI Text
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.55,0:27:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Input.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.11,0:27:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In such way, user won't be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.58,0:27:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,interrupted by selecting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.14,0:27:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.86,0:27:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The user can spend more time to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.51,0:27:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.87,0:27:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't dive into too much about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.16,0:27:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization stuff, but
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.11,0:27:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're interested, please
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.96,0:27:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,watch Internationalization Best
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.81,0:27:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Practices from last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.37,0:27:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Last but not least, hardware
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.29,0:27:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.73,0:28:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I think everyone use hardware
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.16,0:28:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard and I believe you all
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.02,0:28:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,love the keyboard shortcuts,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.88,0:28:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,like Command C, Command V,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.70,0:28:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,probably your favorite is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.62,0:28:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Command Z.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.42,0:28:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We brought that to iOS with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.31,0:28:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Smart Keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.40,0:28:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS, you can define your
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.21,0:28:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,own shortcut for your user if I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.07,0:28:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have iPad app.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.91,0:28:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see, how we do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.29,0:28:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's dive right into the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.10,0:28:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very straightforward and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.26,0:28:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.80,0:28:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, in UI Responder, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.88,0:28:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,override the key commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.65,0:28:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Key commands return an array of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.12,0:28:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,key commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.64,0:28:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That means you can define a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.10,0:28:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,couple shortcuts for your app at
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.75,0:28:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.74,0:28:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To define a key command is very
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.74,0:28:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.51,0:28:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it inputs.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.16,0:28:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You give a modifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.17,0:28:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You put your selector there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.04,0:28:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then also give it a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.01,0:28:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, don't forget to localize
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.27,0:28:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.28,0:29:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our second shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.29,0:29:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, press on the Command key,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.24,0:29:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it will display the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.32,0:29:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,shortcut for you and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.07,0:29:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can see in our CatChat app, we
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.20,0:29:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have Command Up and Command Down
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.52,0:29:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to switch between the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.72,0:29:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.07,0:29:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's recap.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.39,0:29:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've talked about the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.22,0:29:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,multilingual problem to how to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.72,0:29:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,give your app a memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.35,0:29:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've talked about how to take
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.61,0:29:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,most advantages out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.36,0:29:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,context for predictions by
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.77,0:29:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,giving your text field a tag
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.91,0:29:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,through text content type.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.84,0:29:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I talked about the new smartness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.16,0:29:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for text input fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.43,0:29:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I also talked about the mark
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.49,0:29:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,text.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.85,0:29:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Last but not least, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.84,0:29:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard shortcuts you'll want
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.00,0:29:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to try out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.66,0:29:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Try them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.90,0:29:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, James is going to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.51,0:29:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about how to create a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.93,0:29:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,input views.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.00,0:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,James?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.52,0:30:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.07,0:30:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Shuchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.27,0:30:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very nervous -- I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.45,0:30:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,excited to tell you about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.88,0:30:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,creating custom input views.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.43,0:30:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Shuchen briefly mentioned a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.95,0:30:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Responder property called
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.73,0:30:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Keyboard Type, which allows you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.27,0:30:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to access a lot of the built-in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.59,0:30:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS system keyboards for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.16,0:30:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,specialized input, such as the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.51,0:30:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,decimal pad for entering decimal
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.96,0:30:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers, and we also have a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.68,0:30:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,phone pad for entering phone
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.01,0:30:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers, and a special keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.92,0:30:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,just for URLs and email
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.37,0:30:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.57,0:30:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes though, this may not
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.77,0:30:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,be enough for your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.65,0:30:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You may want to go beyond what
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.07,0:30:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the system keyboard provides
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.14,0:30:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.03,0:30:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.17,0:30:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.07,0:30:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, mathematics is a pretty good
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.27,0:30:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.16,0:30:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In math, there's a lot of custom
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.31,0:30:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,symbols like Greek letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.41,0:30:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,superscript operators, and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.11,0:30:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,subscript operators.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.44,0:30:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be pretty difficult to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.71,0:30:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,type something like this with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.41,0:30:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the built-in system keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.39,0:30:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift Playgrounds is another
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.22,0:30:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,good example.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.43,0:31:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Swift Playgrounds
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.40,0:31:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.56,0:31:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the standard QWERTY
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.87,0:31:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,layout, but they provide a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.28,0:31:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of additional functionality for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.63,0:31:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,frequently used symbols in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.77,0:31:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift programming language.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.81,0:31:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And they also have a really nice
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.01,0:31:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory bar in the top here,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.93,0:31:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for quickly inputting relevant
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.19,0:31:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,functions and symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.92,0:31:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then lastly, Apple numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.22,0:31:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,spreadsheets, is another good
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.32,0:31:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.21,0:31:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a formula entry bar
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.97,0:31:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,here, which also requires a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.32,0:31:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of custom symbols, and they also
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.33,0:31:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,have a nice, dark gray
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.29,0:31:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,background here, so it blends in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.66,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,really nicely with the system
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.86,0:31:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, going back to our CatChat
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.57,0:31:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,app, it's another pretty good
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.82,0:31:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,example for something that needs
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.37,0:31:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a custom input view.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.56,0:31:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Well, right now, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.19,0:31:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,way to talk to our pets, but our
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.59,0:31:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pets don't have a way to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.44,0:31:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,back to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.05,0:31:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's because, they have a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.47,0:31:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of trouble using the QWERTY
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.48,0:31:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.02,0:31:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Their paws are quite large.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.69,0:31:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The keys are really small.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.31,0:31:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, they have a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.89,0:31:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulty hitting those keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.89,0:31:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, they have a really limited
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.42,0:31:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,vocabulary too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.71,0:31:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they don't really need to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.37,0:31:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,say a whole lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.15,0:32:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say we want to make a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.67,0:32:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard just for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.66,0:32:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible to cats and dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.97,0:32:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, maybe we want just large
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.46,0:32:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,graphical buttons to represent
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.52,0:32:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,their entire small vocabulary.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.45,0:32:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's what that might look
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.22,0:32:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,like.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.02,0:32:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our PetChat app, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.00,0:32:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the -- it's got the cool,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.51,0:32:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,expanding text view that Kasia
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.32,0:32:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,built for us earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.76,0:32:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, on the pet side, we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.48,0:32:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,have three, large graphical
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.68,0:32:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons with -- representing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.43,0:32:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,their entire vocabulary of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.48,0:32:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,things they might want to say
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.40,0:32:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,like, "I need food," "I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.57,0:32:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,go outside," and "Stop petting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.60,0:32:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,me."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.94,0:32:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.44,0:32:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The other cool thing too is that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.02,0:32:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this behaves just like the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.06,0:32:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,system keyboard does.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.80,0:32:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It sits at the bottom of the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.64,0:32:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.52,0:32:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an accessory bar at the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.70,0:32:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,top that's laid out, right at
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.05,0:32:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the top of the -- where the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.66,0:32:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.31,0:32:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then also the scroll view in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the background, automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.84,0:32:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,adapts its content insets to the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.33,0:32:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,size of your custom input view.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.48,0:32:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go into a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.53,0:32:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,more detail, about how to build
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.27,0:32:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.09,0:33:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for our PetChat app, to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.89,0:33:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,create something like this, all
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.82,0:33:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to do is subclass UI
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.83,0:33:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Input View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.30,0:33:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And by doing that, we get a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.73,0:33:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of stuff for free, such as the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,blurry gray background that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.94,0:33:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mimics the system keyboard's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.44,0:33:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.57,0:33:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But most importantly, we provide
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.84,0:33:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you a way to access the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.22,0:33:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,currently interactive text field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.93,0:33:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user has selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.59,0:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do this via a special
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.72,0:33:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,property, called Text Document
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.55,0:33:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Proxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.79,0:33:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Text Document Proxy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.03,0:33:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to access things like
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.77,0:33:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the text input traits for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.10,0:33:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,currently selected text field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.69,0:33:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that would be stuff like
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.66,0:33:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not it's a password
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.10,0:33:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,field, what kind of content type
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.74,0:33:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it prefers, and even what kind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.73,0:33:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of keyboard type it prefers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.74,0:33:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can adapt as necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.00,0:33:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But most importantly, the Text
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.50,0:33:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Proxy also allows you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.29,0:33:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to insert text into the text
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.04,0:33:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,field, via a simple method
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.34,0:33:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,called Insert Text, which just
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.51,0:33:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,takes a string.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.82,0:33:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and one more thing that you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.72,0:33:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,can do with the Text Document
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.85,0:33:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Proxy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.79,0:33:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can access where the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.79,0:33:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,insertion point position is, and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.76,0:33:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the text before and after the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.53,0:33:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,insertion point.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.16,0:33:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.20,0:34:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's talk about how we can
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.73,0:34:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,actually get this inside of our
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.41,0:34:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,PetChat app.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.03,0:34:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go back to our old
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.96,0:34:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,friend here, the conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.56,0:34:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.47,0:34:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to get it to show up in our
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.48,0:34:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation view controller, we
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.91,0:34:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,simply need to instantiate our
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.12,0:34:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,custom input view as a member
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.49,0:34:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.69,0:34:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, override a UI
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.08,0:34:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Responder method called Can
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.23,0:34:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Become First Responder, to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.65,0:34:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,return True, so that it becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.49,0:34:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a part of the responder chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.88,0:34:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then lastly, all we need to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.25,0:34:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,do, is override this other UI
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.56,0:34:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Responder method called Input
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.81,0:34:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,View.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.08,0:34:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then just return our custom
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.06,0:34:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,input view instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.89,0:34:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're using things like
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.11,0:34:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Text View or UI Text Field,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you actually don't need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.57,0:34:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,most of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.78,0:34:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Text View and UI Text Field,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.41,0:34:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the input view property is a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.70,0:34:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,writable property.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.95,0:34:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all you really need to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.09,0:34:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,actually just assign your custom
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.95,0:34:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,input view instance to the input
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.02,0:34:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,view property.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.08,0:34:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now, our pets have a way of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.69,0:34:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,talking back to us in the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.46,0:34:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,PetChat app, but let's say they
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.73,0:34:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,actually do kind of want to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.60,0:34:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,break out a little bit and start
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.03,0:35:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tweeting or maybe writing a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.13,0:35:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.92,0:35:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they have a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.72,0:35:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting things to say with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.78,0:35:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that small vocabulary of theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.35,0:35:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS 8, we actually added
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.87,0:35:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability to create custom
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.43,0:35:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard extensions, so that it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.87,0:35:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,runs anywhere in the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.13,0:35:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually our first time
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.08,0:35:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about it at WWDC.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.80,0:35:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's what our custom
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.09,0:35:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard extension might look
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.22,0:35:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,like, running inside of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.37,0:35:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.41,0:35:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can -- your pets can
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.49,0:35:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,chat anywhere, or type into
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.46,0:35:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Twitter or keep a blog or
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.48,0:35:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.64,0:35:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's actually really easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.46,0:35:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,go from an input view into a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.22,0:35:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,custom keyboard extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.22,0:35:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I'm going to give you a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.54,0:35:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,quick demo and show you how to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.76,0:35:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.63,0:35:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's switch over to the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.46,0:35:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,computer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.53,0:35:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is our custom
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.87,0:35:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,input view controller here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.45,0:35:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to go into too
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.48,0:35:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,much detail about how it was
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.51,0:35:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,built, but our sample code is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.95,0:35:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,uploaded online.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.11,0:35:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can download all this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.19,0:35:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself if you want to take a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.20,0:35:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.92,0:35:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But to take -- let's go ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.67,0:35:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and build and run this first to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.80,0:35:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,see what it looks like inside of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.53,0:36:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Build and run.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.12,0:36:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so here's our custom
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.48,0:36:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,input view running inside of our
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.66,0:36:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.75,0:36:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I'm going to pretend
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.00,0:36:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,like I'm a pet and just start
