Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.74,0:39:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,right underneath there, under
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.86,0:39:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Siri and search that just says,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.04,0:39:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"keyboards."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.10,0:39:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And by clicking this, the user
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.84,0:39:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-- all the user has to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.15,0:39:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,check this one switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.55,0:39:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the keyboard's enabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.52,0:39:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.95,0:39:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.35,0:39:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard developers are going to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.28,0:39:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,love that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.05,0:39:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now, I'm just going to go
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.42,0:39:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,over to messages here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.91,0:39:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I'm going to switch to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.11,0:39:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,our custom keyboard extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.23,0:39:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.86,0:39:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have it running, all over
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.03,0:39:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.12,0:39:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I'm just going to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.18,0:39:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,express how I'm feeling about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.91,0:39:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the demo right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.08,0:39:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.94,0:39:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go back over to the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.70,0:39:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.52,0:39:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.26,0:39:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. So, this is actually my
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.15,0:39:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,personally recommended way for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.62,0:39:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you to develop third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.14,0:39:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.80,0:39:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really easy to test it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.52,0:39:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,inside of your app first, just
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.12,0:39:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as a custom input view.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.53,0:39:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, as you saw, going from
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.13,0:39:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a custom input view to a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.48,0:40:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard extension is really
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.58,0:40:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.07,0:40:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's really the way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.53,0:40:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just a quick recap of how to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.14,0:40:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,convert from a custom input view
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.52,0:40:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to a keyboard extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.14,0:40:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We just made a new target and we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.69,0:40:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,used the Custom Keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.41,0:40:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Extension Template.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.71,0:40:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either fill in the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.89,0:40:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,provided UI Input View
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.12,0:40:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller Subclass, or change
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.17,0:40:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it so that it works with your
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.04,0:40:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,own.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.15,0:40:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then lastly, I showed you a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.21,0:40:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,cool, new user acceleration or a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.40,0:40:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cool new acceleration for your
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.53,0:40:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,users to enable your keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.74,0:40:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,from within your Settings
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.57,0:40:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.46,0:40:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.78,0:40:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a couple of new APIs in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.04,0:40:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 that I want to share with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.64,0:40:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you tonight -- or today.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.42,0:40:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can now access the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.82,0:40:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,currently selected text that the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.45,0:40:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,user has selected, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.07,0:40:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty useful if you want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.42,0:40:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,retro correction with your Auto
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.39,0:40:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Complete Engine, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.33,0:40:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Or provide some kind of cool
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.49,0:40:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,context around the text that the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.41,0:40:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,user had selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.51,0:40:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We also provide you this new
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.58,0:40:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thing called the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.91,0:41:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Identifier Handle, which is just
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.55,0:41:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a UUID, that uniquely identifies
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.20,0:41:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,one text field from the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.36,0:41:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is real useful for a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.85,0:41:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of things, but one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.08,0:41:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,things that it's useful for is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.63,0:41:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for resetting your keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.31,0:41:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,state when the user switches
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.88,0:41:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,text fields, so you can clear
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.68,0:41:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,your predictions if you have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.84,0:41:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,predictions displayed, or switch
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.81,0:41:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the alphabetic plane if
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.49,0:41:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the user had switched to your
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.50,0:41:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,numeric plane, or something like
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.66,0:41:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.18,0:41:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, we also added the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.42,0:41:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,ability for you to query whether
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.60,0:41:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or not the user has granted your
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.82,0:41:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,extension full access.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.30,0:41:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll go over what full
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.42,0:41:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,access means in just a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.45,0:41:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in case you're not familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.50,0:41:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, I want to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.48,0:41:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,some other lesser known,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.76,0:41:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,third-party keyboard APIs that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.04,0:41:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe you didn't know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.22,0:41:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS 10, we actually added
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.99,0:41:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.89,0:41:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,incorporate the System Globe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.78,0:41:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Menu inside of your keyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.92,0:41:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really nice so that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.15,0:41:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your user can quickly switch
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.47,0:41:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,between all of the keyboards
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.90,0:41:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.65,0:41:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lot better than that next
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.86,0:41:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard thing that we had
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.73,0:41:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.25,0:41:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.52,0:41:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.02,0:42:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also personalize your
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.33,0:42:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,auto complete results with
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,something that we call the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.07,0:42:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Supplementary Lexicon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.67,0:42:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Supplementary Lexicon is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.07,0:42:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,basically just a list of words
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.65,0:42:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,containing the portion of the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.84,0:42:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,user's address book, so you can
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.61,0:42:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,auto complete various names and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.45,0:42:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff, that the user might be
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.55,0:42:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,referencing in the text that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.16,0:42:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they type.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.55,0:42:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, tying back to some
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.84,0:42:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of the multilingual support that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.14,0:42:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we added in iOS 11, that Shuchen
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.39,0:42:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was talking about earlier, your
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.77,0:42:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard can use those document
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.17,0:42:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier handle things that I
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.49,0:42:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was mentioning before, as a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.86,0:42:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,multilingual hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.71,0:42:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if your keyboard supports
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.52,0:42:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple languages, you too can
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.08,0:42:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,behave like the system keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.31,0:42:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,does, and change when
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.54,0:42:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.53,0:42:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, lastly, we can't talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.05,0:42:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,third-party keyboard extensions
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.47,0:42:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,without talking about privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.75,0:42:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and user trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.19,0:42:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, privacy is very much a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.94,0:42:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,standard iOS feature that users
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.42,0:42:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.97,0:42:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And users are made aware that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.85,0:42:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,all of their keystrokes are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.93,0:42:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,handled by your extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.55,0:42:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're doing something
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.43,0:42:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with those keystrokes, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.89,0:42:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,sending them offsite or
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.54,0:43:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing them in some way, you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.06,0:43:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,should make sure to inform the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.07,0:43:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,user about this, and anonymize
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.72,0:43:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the data that's coming in, if
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.87,0:43:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you are sending it offsite.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.86,0:43:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, most applications
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.98,0:43:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't actually need it, but
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.35,0:43:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask the user to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.23,0:43:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your extension with full access,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.28,0:43:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which means access to some lower
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.67,0:43:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,level parts of the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.27,0:43:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk a little bit about
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.83,0:43:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what full access really means.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.65,0:43:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first of all, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.08,0:43:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,actually quite a bit of value in
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.58,0:43:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,not asking for full access.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.36,0:43:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why we built the full
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.63,0:43:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,access switch to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.72,0:43:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a speed bump for you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.13,0:43:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.91,0:43:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, our Apple customers are
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.59,0:43:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,very privacy conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.61,0:43:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, your keyboards already
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.95,0:43:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,provide a lot of awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.90,0:43:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality right out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.81,0:43:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,box, without full access.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.83,0:43:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, granting this should really
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.78,0:43:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,only supplement your existing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.15,0:43:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,feature set.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.07,0:43:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, some examples of things that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.40,0:43:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you might need full access for,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.64,0:43:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is communicating with your main
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.83,0:43:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.87,0:43:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you need to build a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.65,0:43:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,bridge from your main app bundle
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.38,0:43:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to your custom keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.35,0:43:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,extension, if you want to access
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.74,0:43:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like a database or something
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.80,0:43:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have stored there,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.05,0:43:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll need to request for full
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.26,0:43:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,access for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.05,0:44:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to access a -- if
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.67,0:44:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to provide your user
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.24,0:44:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with a repository of gif images
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.78,0:44:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance, then you'll need
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.64,0:44:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask for full access to grant
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.94,0:44:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,access to the networking stack
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.60,0:44:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.02,0:44:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for current location, in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.03,0:44:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,case you want to enrich your
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.46,0:44:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,auto complete results with
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.27,0:44:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,references to locations that the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.84,0:44:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,user might be referencing to in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.78,0:44:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the text that they type, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.49,0:44:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,need to request for full access
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.01,0:44:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for the current location.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.11,0:44:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll also have to have the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.35,0:44:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,user grant your main app access
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.10,0:44:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to your current location too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.33,0:44:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.71,0:44:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the address book, most
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.58,0:44:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,applications don't actually need
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.91,0:44:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,this because of what I said
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.21,0:44:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about the supplementary lexicon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.28,0:44:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you actually don't need full
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.77,0:44:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,access to get to the address
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.75,0:44:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,book.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.37,0:44:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you want to access some
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.45,0:44:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,more of the address book, like
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.67,0:44:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the notes fields, or nickname,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.52,0:44:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.50,0:44:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you will need full access
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.45,0:44:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.07,0:44:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, make sure that your
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.33,0:44:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard works without
